    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nOpenning terminal with `:vertical terminal`, `:belowright terminal`, `:aboveleft terminal` \r\ndoesn't put the terminal at expected location and equal size with existing. Instead it takes the whole buffer space.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nnvim --clean :vertical terminal :belowright terminal :aboveleft terminal\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n3 terminal windows are displayed on screen.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1302\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-03-29 at 15 49 09\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/13009812/d59eb658-116e-41ac-bf9a-7bbc7f76071d\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.5\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\n9.0.1894\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nterminal 2.14\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
